text: Nassarius arcadioi is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae, the Nassa mud snails or dog whelks. ==Description== The shell grows to a length of 25 mm. ==Distribution== This species occurs in the Atlantic Ocean off Mauritania. ==References== * Rolán E. & Hernández J.M. (2005) The West African species of the group Nassarius denticulatus (Mollusca, Neogastropoda), with the description of a new species. Journal of Conchology 38(5): 499–511. page(s): 507 ==External links== * Category:Nassariidae Category:Gastropods described in 2005
title: Nassarius arcadioi
